Class ShortArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.PrimitiveCollection
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveArray
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.scalars.ShortArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, ShortIterable, PrimitiveList, ShortList, ShortCollection, Initializable, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, CompressibleCollection
    public final class ShortArray
extends PrimitiveArray
implements ShortList
    A dynamic array of primitive short values. Supports the indexing operations in ShortList. Expands the size of the array if you call set(int, short) or add(short) and the array is not big enough.

    Constructors take the same name, maximum size and estimated capacity that all PrimitiveCollections take. In addition a ShortArray can construct from part or all of a primitive short[].

    A sub-array can be retrieved by specifying the starting index and the length with subArray(int, int). The sub-array is read only and will share data with the underlying parent array for efficiency.

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    PrimitiveCollection, ShortList, KryoSerializable, CompressibleCollection, CompressibleCollection
